race.comment: Tough to sort this one out with many either on debut or first-up from a spell and BUTTERCUP (8) looks well-placed at the first run of the second prep. Was close to a win before a break, starting favourite at the latest appearance and finishing second at Casterton. Placed in a recent trial and, significantly, the blinkers go on. SWEATBAND (6) finished third last start over 1100m at Ararat, beaten 4.5 lengths. This is a nice drop in grade so he is a major player. ALVIN (1) showed good early dash and raced on the speed last start before fading to finish 6 lengths back in 11th over 1200m at Seymour. Will take some beating. ELLYETTTE (9) has run adequately without really threatening in most starts this campaign, but they've been in stronger races than this, so she looks to get her best chance of a win from a gun draw. SHAME ON SUE (10) is another who's been right around the mark this prep, but does have a tricky alley to contend with.
